## Overview

[**esolang-box**](https://github.com/hakatashi/esolang-box) provides a consistent, Docker-based interface for running <%= language_count %> programming languages — from mainstream languages to obscure [esoteric programming languages](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Esoteric_programming_language).

Every image in the collection follows the same interface:

* **First argument** — path to the source code file
* **stdin** — program input
* **stdout** — program output

This means you can switch between languages without changing how you invoke them. All images are available under the [`esolang/` namespace on Docker Hub](https://hub.docker.com/u/esolang/).

The `<%= slug %>` command (also aliased as `script`) runs the <%= name %> interpreter inside this image.

## Usage

### Run a script

<% if hello_content.nil? %>
```sh
$ ls
<%= hello_file %>

$ docker run --rm -v "$PWD":/code:ro esolang/<%= slug %> <%= slug %> /code/<%= hello_file %>
<%= hello_out %>
```
<% else %>
```sh
$ cat <%= hello_file %>
<%= hello_content %>
$ docker run --rm -v "$PWD":/code:ro esolang/<%= slug %> <%= slug %> /code/<%= hello_file %>
<%= hello_out %>
```
<% end %>

### Pass input via stdin

```sh
$ docker run -i --rm -v "$PWD":/code:ro esolang/<%= slug %> <%= slug %> /code/<%= hello_file %> < input.txt
```

### Open an interactive shell

Useful for debugging or exploring the image environment.

```sh
$ docker run -it --rm -v "$PWD":/code:ro esolang/<%= slug %> sh
# <%= slug %> /code/<%= hello_file %>
<%= hello_out %>
```

### Trace exec syscalls with strace

esolang-box supports tracing `execve` and `execveat` syscalls. Set the `STRACE_OUTPUT_PATH` environment variable and grant the `SYS_PTRACE` capability to write a strace log to the specified path.

```sh
$ docker run --cap-add=SYS_PTRACE --rm -v "$PWD":/code \
    --env STRACE_OUTPUT_PATH=/code/strace.txt \
    esolang/<%= slug %> <%= slug %> /code/<%= hello_file %>
<%= hello_out %>
```

**Notes:**

* On kernels older than 4.8, [enabling ptrace disables the seccomp filter](https://bugs.chromium.org/p/project-zero/issues/detail?id=1718). Avoid using `--cap-add=SYS_PTRACE` on such systems (e.g. Ubuntu Xenial).
* Strace adds significant overhead — syscalls may run roughly 10× slower than normal.

<% if disasm %>
### Disassemble a script

This image includes a `disasm` command that converts a <%= name %> program into a more human-readable form.

```sh
$ docker run --rm -v "$PWD":/code:ro esolang/<%= slug %> disasm /code/<%= hello_file %>
```
<% end %>
